definition: mountain pass/to close/to shut/to turn off/to concern/to involve
rampart/base (in baseball)/to build with stones, bricks etc

sentences.english: The government has raised tariff walls against foreign goods.
sentences.chinese: 政府已建立關稅壁壘以抵制舶來品。

sentences.english: But observers are not expecting the countries’ lucrative customs posts to be dismantled.
sentences.chinese: 但是觀察員並不期望各國撤除利潤豐厚的關稅壁壘。

sentences.english: For the erection of tariff walls has the same effect as the erection of real walls.
sentences.chinese: 設立關稅壁壘的效果，跟築牆擋道沒有兩樣。

sentences.english: The government decided to raise tariff walls against foreign goods.
sentences.chinese: 政府決定提高關稅壁壘以抵制外國貨。
